Interface SimplePropertyList

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, fr.ens.biologie.generic.DataContainer, PropertyListGetters, PropertyListSetters, ReadOnlyPropertyList, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Sizeable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ExtendablePropertyList, SimpleWriteProtectablePropertyList
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CompoundPropertyListImpl, ExtendablePropertyListImpl, SharedPropertyListImpl, SharedWriteProtectablePropertyListImpl, SimplePropertyListImpl
    public interface SimplePropertyList
extends PropertyListSetters, ReadOnlyPropertyList

    Simple, straightforward read-write property list for graph GraphElements. A property list is just a list of (name,value) pairs, where name is a String and value is any descendant of Object (including primitive types).

    1. Immutable.
    2. Default properties: none.
    Author:
    Jacques Gignoux - 23-10-2018
